{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BoMcEs6b9PiDpJR8a1Wvu8","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Block 01: OTA (Folded-Cascode) — Requirements\n     2→\n     3→## Software Required\n     4→\n     5→| Tool | Version | Purpose |\n     6→|------|---------|---------|\n     7→| ngspice | ≥42 | SPICE simulation (DC, AC, transient, noise, STB) |\n     8→| Xschem | ≥3.4 | Schematic capture |\n     9→| Magic | ≥8.3 | Layout, DRC, PEX |\n    10→| KLayout | ≥0.29 | Layout viewing |\n    11→| Netgen | ≥1.5 | LVS |\n    12→| Python 3 | ≥3.10 | Post-processing |\n    13→| matplotlib | ≥3.7 | Plotting (Bode plots, noise spectra) |\n    14→| numpy | ≥1.24 | Numerical analysis |\n    15→\n    16→## PDK\n    17→SkyWater SKY130A\n    18→\n    19→## Dependencies\n    20→Block 00 (bias generator) provides Iref=500nA. For initial development, use an ideal current source `Ibias 0 vbias 500n` and replace with Block 00 output later.\n    21→\n    22→## Outputs Produced\n    23→| File | Description |\n    24→|------|-------------|\n    25→| `ota_foldcasc.sch` | Xschem schematic |\n    26→| `ota_foldcasc.spice` | SPICE netlist (subcircuit, reusable) |\n    27→| `tb_ota_ac.spice` | Open-loop AC analysis (gain, BW, PM) |\n    28→| `tb_ota_noise.spice` | Noise analysis |\n    29→| `tb_ota_dc.spice` | DC sweep (output swing, linearity) |\n    30→| `tb_ota_tran.spice` | Step response (slew, settling) |\n    31→| `tb_ota_psrr.spice` | PSRR measurement |\n    32→| `tb_ota_cmrr.spice` | CMRR measurement |\n    33→| `tb_ota_corners.spice` | 5-corner + 3-temperature sweep |\n    34→| `tb_ota_mc.spice` | Monte Carlo (200 runs) for offset |\n    35→| `results.md` | All specs, PASS/FAIL, operating points |\n    36→| `ota_foldcasc.mag` | Magic layout |\n    37→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01e4b3b1-6a11-48e6-b3e7-40758ef8985d","uuid":"253d8e81-40fc-4922-825b-e024e65ef7d8","timestamp":"2026-03-22T21:51:07.144Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/vibrosense/01_ota/requirements.md","content":"# Block 01: OTA (Folded-Cascode) — Requirements\n\n## Software Required\n\n| Tool | Version | Purpose |\n|------|---------|---------|\n| ngspice | ≥42 | SPICE simulation (DC, AC, transient, noise, STB) |\n| Xschem | ≥3.4 | Schematic capture |\n| Magic | ≥8.3 | Layout, DRC, PEX |\n| KLayout | ≥0.29 | Layout viewing |\n| Netgen | ≥1.5 | LVS |\n| Python 3 | ≥3.10 | Post-processing |\n| matplotlib | ≥3.7 | Plotting (Bode plots, noise spectra) |\n| numpy | ≥1.24 | Numerical analysis |\n\n## PDK\nSkyWater SKY130A\n\n## Dependencies\nBlock 00 (bias generator) provides Iref=500nA. For initial development, use an ideal current source `Ibias 0 vbias 500n` and replace with Block 00 output later.\n\n## Outputs Produced\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `ota_foldcasc.sch` | Xschem schematic |\n| `ota_foldcasc.spice` | SPICE netlist (subcircuit, reusable) |\n| `tb_ota_ac.spice` | Open-loop AC analysis (gain, BW, PM) |\n| `tb_ota_noise.spice` | Noise analysis |\n| `tb_ota_dc.spice` | DC sweep (output swing, linearity) |\n| `tb_ota_tran.spice` | Step response (slew, settling) |\n| `tb_ota_psrr.spice` | PSRR measurement |\n| `tb_ota_cmrr.spice` | CMRR measurement |\n| `tb_ota_corners.spice` | 5-corner + 3-temperature sweep |\n| `tb_ota_mc.spice` | Monte Carlo (200 runs) for offset |\n| `results.md` | All specs, PASS/FAIL, operating points |\n| `ota_foldcasc.mag` | Magic layout |\n","numLines":37,"startLine":1,"totalLines":37}}}
