{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01DKhozxWw62h5MTNnsS2W3u","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found it. The expressions use uppercase `MC_MM_SWITCH` and `AGAUSS`. But my .param defines lowercase `mc_mm_switch`. In ngspice, parameter names are case-insensitive by default, so this should work... but let me check.\n\nActually, the bigger issue is that even with MC_MM_SWITCH=0, ngspice tries to fully evaluate the expression `{4.148e-09+MC_MM_SWITCH*AGAUSS(0,1.0,1)*(4.148e-09*1.0*(sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8__toxe_slope/sqrt(l*w*mult)))}` at parse time. Since `l`, `w`, and `mult` are instance parameters, they're not available when parsing the `.model` statement.\n\n\nThis is a fundamental limitation with how ngspice handles the SKY130 PDK model files. I need to preprocess the model files to strip out the mismatch terms entirely, replacing expressions like `+MC_MM_SWITCH*AGAUSS(...)*(...)` with just `0` so that `toxe = {4.148e-09+0}` becomes `toxe = 4.148e-09`.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":670,"cache_read_input_tokens":129371,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":670},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01e4b3b1-6a11-48e6-b3e7-40758ef8985d","uuid":"1106b3c4-9fe7-4415-b516-1913cf327b7a"}
