{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_013xgpwAL4TaQhwQLCrALDd3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Excellent data! Let me analyze the Vbcp sweep:\n\n- Vbcp=0.85: Vout=0.928V, M6_Vds=0.825V, M4_Vds=0.047V ← M4 in triode\n- Vbcp=0.90: Vout=0.512V, M6_Vds=1.263V, M4_Vds=0.026V ← M4 deep triode, output drops sharply\n\n\n- The output collapses dramatically between these two points, dropping from 0.928V to 0.512V. I need to find the exact Vbcp value where Vout hits 0.9V, which appears to be right around 0.85 where M6 is still well-saturated but M4 is already starting to push into triode.\n\n- The Vbcn sweep shows it's not the limiting factor here—output stays stable around 0.975V across the range, so Vbcp is really the control knob I need to adjust. At Vbcp around 0.87, I might get closer to my 0.9V target, though I'm concerned that M4 will remain in triode, which could be problematic for the circuit's operation.\n\nThe real issue is that M4 isn't functioning as a proper current source—with mid_n sitting at 1.753V and VDD at 1.8V, the voltage drop across M4 is only 0.047V, well below saturation. This happens because M6 is dropping a large voltage due to the strong gate-source drive from Vbcp, pushing mid_n too high and starving M4 of headroom.\n\nTo keep M4 in saturation, I need mid_n below 1.738V, which constrains M6's source-drain voltage to less than 0.810V. At the current Vbcp=0.85V, M6 drops 0.825V, pushing M4 right to the edge of triode operation. I could fix this by reducing the saturation voltage of M3/M4 through sizing adjustments, or by lowering the fold current to give M4 more breathing room. Alternatively, if the AC performance holds up, I might tolerate M4 being slightly in triode.\n\nThe real bottleneck here is that 76mV offset—that's what's constraining my design space. Let me set Vbcp around 0.87V and run an AC analysis to measure the open-loop gain. Since I'm just characterizing the amplifier's frequency response, I can skip the feedback loop and test it open-loop directly.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1273,"cache_read_input_tokens":225359,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1273},"output_tokens":39,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01e4b3b1-6a11-48e6-b3e7-40758ef8985d","uuid":"1e7e386b-2723-4961-9e52-b35e12e0762e"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_013xgpwAL4TaQhwQLCrALDd3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good data. Vbcp=0.85 gives Vout=0.928V (close to 0.9V). Let me fine-tune Vbcp and then proceed directly to the AC testbench, which is the key performance metric."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1273,"cache_read_input_tokens":225359,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1273},"output_tokens":39,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01e4b3b1-6a11-48e6-b3e7-40758ef8985d","uuid":"b24e2d7d-33e6-4164-b497-2fcf046db43b"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_013xgpwAL4TaQhwQLCrALDd3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_0126TcHj4SrKu9qjGPaZ8mSw","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/vibrosense/01_ota/tb_ota_ac.spice","content":"* ============================================================\n* TB01: AC Open-Loop Analysis — VibroSense OTA\n* Measures: DC gain, UGB, phase margin, gain margin\n* ============================================================\n\n.lib \"sky130_minimal.lib.spice\" tt\n.include \"ota_foldcasc.spice\"\n\n.param vdd_val = 1.8\n.param vcm_val = 0.9\n\nVdd vdd 0 dc {vdd_val}\nVss vss 0 dc 0\n\n* Bias generation\nMbn vbn vbn 0 0 sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8__model W=4u L=4u nf=1\nIbias vdd vbn dc 500n\nVbcn vbcn 0 dc 0.80\nMbp vbp vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8__model W=8u L=1u nf=2\nIbp vbp 0 dc 500n\nVbcp vbcp 0 dc 0.85\n\n* AC stimulus: apply differential input around common-mode\n* Use a large inductor to set DC operating point while allowing AC signal\nVcm cm 0 dc {vcm_val}\nVac vinp cm dc 0 ac 1\n\n* For the inverting input, use unity-gain feedback with DC bias\n* The large inductor blocks AC but passes DC for bias\nLfb vout vinn 1G\nRdc vinn cm 0\n\n* Instantiate OTA\nXota vinp vinn vout vdd vss vbn vbcn vbp vbcp ota_foldcasc\nCL vout 0 10p\n\n* DC operating point first, then AC sweep\n.op\n.ac dec 100 1 100Meg\n\n.control\n  run\n\n  echo \"\"\n  echo \"======================================================\"\n  echo \"  AC ANALYSIS — VibroSense Folded-Cascode OTA\"\n  echo \"======================================================\"\n\n  * DC operating point\n  echo \"--- DC Operating Point ---\"\n  print v(vout) v(vbn) v(vbp)\n\n  * Gain\n  meas ac gain_db MAX vdb(vout)\n  meas ac freq_3db WHEN vdb(vout)='gain_db-3' FALL=1\n\n  * Unity-gain bandwidth\n  meas ac ugb WHEN vdb(vout)=0 FALL=1\n\n  * Phase at UGB\n  meas ac phase_at_ugb FIND vp(vout) AT=ugb\n\n  * Phase margin\n  let pm = phase_at_ugb + 180\n  echo \"Phase margin:\"\n  print pm\n\n  * Gain margin\n  meas ac freq_neg180 WHEN vp(vout)=-180 FALL=1\n  meas ac gain_at_neg180 FIND vdb(vout) AT=freq_neg180\n  let gm_margin = -gain_at_neg180\n  echo \"Gain margin (dB):\"\n  print gm_margin\n\n  echo \"\"\n  echo \"======================================================\"\n\n  * Save Bode plot data\n  wrdata bode_data vdb(vout) vp(vout)\n\n  quit\n.endc\n\n.end\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1273,"cache_read_input_tokens":225359,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1273},"output_tokens":39,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01e4b3b1-6a11-48e6-b3e7-40758ef8985d","uuid":"587d9bfe-84c3-4d7f-9a09-a8fc52194f7d"}
