{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01F4t4hspFmvKrwhsjfoUhoj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, that's not right either. Using `Cblock vinn cm 100G` would pass AC and block DC — opposite of what I want. I need vinn at AC ground.\n\nThe correct approach for open-loop AC measurement with DC bias:\n1. At DC: vinn = vout (unity-gain feedback for bias point)\n2. At AC: vinn = Vcm (AC ground, no AC feedback)Use:\n- Lfb (1GH) from vout to vinn → passes DC, blocks AC ✓\n- No additional connection needed if Lfb already sets the DC point\n\n\nBut now I'm realizing the inductor alone leaves vinn floating at AC, so I need to ground it somehow. Adding a large resistor from vinn to the common mode voltage would provide the AC path, but then I've got competing DC paths — the inductor trying to tie vinn to vout while the resistor pulls it toward the bias point.\n\nActually, the standard approach for open-loop AC measurements is simpler: bias the OTA in unity-gain feedback at DC to set the operating point, then break the loop at AC using the inductor. The large resistor provides the AC ground path that the inductor can't offer, and at DC equilibrium everything settles to vout = 0.9V as intended. A 1 megohm resistor should work fine here since the OTA's input impedance is already quite high from the MOS gate structure, so it won't create a loading problem at DC.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":780,"cache_read_input_tokens":229226,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":780},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01e4b3b1-6a11-48e6-b3e7-40758ef8985d","uuid":"6067de4a-5893-41f9-8a4f-cdc666f1352e"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01F4t4hspFmvKrwhsjfoUhoj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01RuU3Soh74RsotjBxXZsLiU","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/vibrosense/01_ota/tb_ota_ac.spice","content":"* ============================================================\n* TB01: AC Open-Loop Analysis — VibroSense OTA\n* ============================================================\n* Method: DC feedback via inductor, AC open-loop\n* Lfb (1GH) passes DC from vout to vinn for bias\n* At AC, Lfb is high-Z so loop is open\n* Vinn is AC-grounded through Vcm source\n* ============================================================\n\n.lib \"sky130_minimal.lib.spice\" tt\n.include \"ota_foldcasc.spice\"\n\n.param vdd_val = 1.8\n.param vcm_val = 0.9\n\nVdd vdd 0 dc {vdd_val}\nVss vss 0 dc 0\n\n* Bias generation\nMbn vbn vbn 0 0 sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8__model W=4u L=4u nf=1\nIbias vdd vbn dc 500n\nVbcn vbcn 0 dc 0.80\nMbp vbp vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8__model W=8u L=1u nf=2\nIbp vbp 0 dc 500n\nVbcp vbcp 0 dc 0.85\n\n* Common-mode voltage\nVcm cm 0 dc {vcm_val}\n\n* AC stimulus on positive input\nVac vinp cm dc 0 ac 1\n\n* DC feedback loop (sets operating point)\nLfb vout fb_node 1G\nRfb fb_node vinn 1\n* Tie vinn to cm through large resistor (DC path + AC ground)\nRbias vinn cm 1G\n\n* Instantiate OTA\nXota vinp vinn vout vdd vss vbn vbcn vbp vbcp ota_foldcasc\nCL vout 0 10p\n\n.ac dec 100 1 100Meg\n\n.control\n  run\n\n  echo \"\"\n  echo \"======================================================\"\n  echo \"  AC ANALYSIS — VibroSense OTA (Open-Loop)\"\n  echo \"======================================================\"\n\n  * DC gain\n  meas ac gain_db MAX vdb(vout)\n  print gain_db\n\n  * 3dB bandwidth\n  meas ac freq_3db WHEN vdb(vout)='gain_db-3' FALL=1\n\n  * Unity-gain bandwidth\n  meas ac ugb WHEN vdb(vout)=0 FALL=1\n  print ugb\n\n  * Phase at UGB\n  meas ac phase_at_ugb FIND vp(vout) AT=ugb\n  print phase_at_ugb\n\n  * Phase margin = phase_at_ugb + 180\n  echo \"Phase Margin:\"\n  let pm = phase_at_ugb + 180\n  print pm\n\n  * Gain at -180 degrees phase\n  meas ac freq_neg180 WHEN vp(vout)=-180 FALL=1\n  meas ac gain_at_neg180 FIND vdb(vout) AT=freq_neg180\n  echo \"Gain Margin (dB):\"\n  let gm_db = -gain_at_neg180\n  print gm_db\n\n  echo \"======================================================\"\n\n  * Save plot data\n  wrdata bode_data vdb(vout) vp(vout)\n\n  quit\n.endc\n\n.end\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":780,"cache_read_input_tokens":229226,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":780},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01e4b3b1-6a11-48e6-b3e7-40758ef8985d","uuid":"396b79d2-4b0c-4e1d-b7ef-839bf3617f63"}
