{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01AfHbtq4iYHVJ8L4NtSKyFn","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The gain is -70 dB at low frequencies. Negative gain means the output is MUCH smaller than the input. And the phase is 0 degrees (not 180), so it's not inverting — just attenuating.\n\nThis means the OTA is not amplifying at all. With the open-loop configuration (Vinn_bias connecting vinn to cm), the output should show the open-loop gain. But instead, we see -70 dB, which means the circuit is severely degraded.\n\nThe problem must be the DC operating point. With vinn = vinp = 0.9V (both tied to cm), and Vbp=0.855, the output settles at Vout≈0.5V (from the OP sweep). \n\nIn the AC test, the voltage source Vinn_bias locks vinn at 0.9V while vinp varies, creating a differential signal that should be amplified. But if the DC operating point has pushed the output devices into triode or away from the linear region, the small-signal gain collapses. I need to verify where the output stage is actually operating.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1845,"cache_read_input_tokens":248398,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1845},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01e4b3b1-6a11-48e6-b3e7-40758ef8985d","uuid":"266a6bc8-1ddb-4717-bdee-8596757e501f"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01AfHbtq4iYHVJ8L4NtSKyFn","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_018Xurx6t77J4djpeKjffKXD","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cat > quick_op.spice << 'EOF'\n.lib \"sky130_minimal.lib.spice\" tt\n.include \"ota_foldcasc.spice\"\n\nVdd vdd 0 dc 1.8\nVss vss 0 dc 0\nVbn  vbn  0 dc 0.58\nVbcn vbcn 0 dc 0.80\nVbp  vbp  0 dc 0.855\nVbcp vbcp 0 dc 0.65\nVinp vinp 0 dc 0.9\nVinn vinn 0 dc 0.9\n\nXota vinp vinn vout vdd vss vbn vbcn vbp vbcp ota_foldcasc\nCL vout 0 10p\n\n.op\n.control\n  run\n  echo \"Vout = $&v(vout)\"\n  echo \"M1 Id=$&@m.xota.m1[id] Vds=$&@m.xota.m1[vds]\"\n  echo \"M2 Id=$&@m.xota.m2[id] Vds=$&@m.xota.m2[vds]\"\n  echo \"M4 Id=$&@m.xota.m4[id] Vds=$&@m.xota.m4[vds] Vdsat=$&@m.xota.m4[vdsat]\"\n  echo \"M6 Id=$&@m.xota.m6[id] Vds=$&@m.xota.m6[vds] Vdsat=$&@m.xota.m6[vdsat]\"\n  echo \"M8 Id=$&@m.xota.m8[id] Vds=$&@m.xota.m8[vds] Vdsat=$&@m.xota.m8[vdsat]\"\n  echo \"M10 Id=$&@m.xota.m10[id] Vds=$&@m.xota.m10[vds] Vdsat=$&@m.xota.m10[vdsat]\"\n  echo \"M11 Id=$&@m.xota.m11[id] Vds=$&@m.xota.m11[vds] Vdsat=$&@m.xota.m11[vdsat]\"\n  quit\n.endc\n.end\nEOF\n/usr/bin/ngspice -b quick_op.spice 2>&1 | grep -E \"^(Vout|M[0-9])\" | head -15","description":"Check OP at open-loop bias","timeout":60000},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1845,"cache_read_input_tokens":248398,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1845},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01e4b3b1-6a11-48e6-b3e7-40758ef8985d","uuid":"dc72dbdc-a3b4-43fe-ad8e-189c0b322024"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018Xurx6t77J4djpeKjffKXD","type":"tool_result","content":"Vout = 0.0554713\nM1 Id=1.81497E-07 Vds=0.000305581\nM2 Id=1.81497E-07 Vds=0.000305581\nM4 Id=3.17509E-07 Vds=0.227408 Vdsat=0.0564167\nM6 Id=3.43579E-07 Vds=1.51712 Vdsat=0.0528002\nM8 Id=1.62084E-07 Vds=0.00094077 Vdsat=0.109488\nM10 Id=1.62084E-07 Vds=0.0545305 Vdsat=0.0706637\nM11 Id=3.62994E-07 Vds=0.0551657 Vdsat=0.0719398","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01e4b3b1-6a11-48e6-b3e7-40758ef8985d","uuid":"9b7a9c06-2cdd-437d-97f0-43ca4985fb0e","timestamp":"2026-03-22T22:43:45.155Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"Vout = 0.0554713\nM1 Id=1.81497E-07 Vds=0.000305581\nM2 Id=1.81497E-07 Vds=0.000305581\nM4 Id=3.17509E-07 Vds=0.227408 Vdsat=0.0564167\nM6 Id=3.43579E-07 Vds=1.51712 Vdsat=0.0528002\nM8 Id=1.62084E-07 Vds=0.00094077 Vdsat=0.109488\nM10 Id=1.62084E-07 Vds=0.0545305 Vdsat=0.0706637\nM11 Id=3.62994E-07 Vds=0.0551657 Vdsat=0.0719398","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01UjeCCJMprCvohdjnobM9oz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"At Vbp=0.855:\n- Vout = 0.055V — near ground!\n- M1/M2: Vds = 0.0003V — DEEP triode! Almost shorted.\n- M8: Vds = 0.0009V — deep triode\n- M10: Vds = 0.055V < Vdsat=0.071V — triode\n- M11: Vds = 0.055V < Vdsat=0.072V — triode\n\nThe output is near ground because the PMOS fold current is LESS than needed. \n\nThe fold branch current from M3/M4 falls short—delivering only ~317nA when the NMOS side needs ~344nA total—so the output gets pulled down to ground. This reveals the circuit is bistable: around Vbp≈0.82 the PMOS dominates and Vout rails high, but around Vbp≈0.86 the PMOS weakens and Vout crashes to ground, with no stable equilibrium between these extremes.\n\nThe positive feedback loop is the culprit. When Vout dips, M2's drain-source voltage shrinks, and if M2 transitions from saturation into triode region, its current collapses—reducing the pull-down current and allowing Vout to recover, which then pushes M2 back into saturation, creating the regenerative action that locks the circuit into one rail or the other.\n\nThe real issue is that the balance point sits at the extremes (around 0.05V or 1.76V) rather than the desired 0.9V, because the tail current and fold current have a sharp crossover with no stable midpoint in open-loop. I could fix this with a proper common-mode feedback circuit, but the unity-gain feedback configuration I tested earlier actually stabilized the output at 0.976V. For AC measurements, I should apply the Middlebrook or Tian technique to extract the loop gain instead of relying on open-loop measurements.\n\nA simpler approach would be to add DC feedback through a very large resistor from the output back to the inverting input—this forces the operating point to 0.9V while keeping the AC feedback negligible, letting me measure the open-loop gain directly from the AC stimulus.\n\nActually, I'm realizing the earlier measurement with feedback only showed 33 dB gain, which seems low. Let me try the most straightforward method: directly connect the output to the inverting input as a unity-gain buffer and measure the loop gain using a voltage source injection technique.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1743,"cache_read_input_tokens":250243,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1743},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01e4b3b1-6a11-48e6-b3e7-40758ef8985d","uuid":"a836aa2b-1d29-41a6-8ae3-2d368314d206"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01UjeCCJMprCvohdjnobM9oz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The circuit is bi-stable open-loop. Let me use a proper closed-loop AC measurement. I'll inject a test signal into the feedback path to measure loop gain."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1743,"cache_read_input_tokens":250243,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1743},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01e4b3b1-6a11-48e6-b3e7-40758ef8985d","uuid":"3b9d1cde-b671-4f06-bdc8-ccf6e64aaec6"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01UjeCCJMprCvohdjnobM9oz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_011s9X5ZNcWxQCAUzcBuW7ot","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/vibrosense/01_ota/tb_ota_ac.spice","content":"* ============================================================\n* TB01: AC Analysis — VibroSense OTA\n* Method: Unity-gain with AC injection for loop gain\n* ============================================================\n\n.lib \"sky130_minimal.lib.spice\" tt\n.include \"ota_foldcasc.spice\"\n\n.param vdd_val = 1.8\n.param vcm_val = 0.9\n\nVdd vdd 0 dc {vdd_val}\nVss vss 0 dc 0\n\n* Bias generation\nMbn vbn vbn 0 0 sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8__model W=4u L=4u nf=1\nIbias vdd vbn dc 500n\nVbcn vbcn 0 dc 0.80\nMbp vbp vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8__model W=8u L=1u nf=2\nIbp vbp 0 dc 500n\nVbcp vbcp 0 dc 0.85\n\n* Input common-mode\nVinp vinp 0 dc {vcm_val} ac 1\n\n* DC feedback through large resistor, AC open loop\n* Rfb provides DC feedback: vout→vinn at DC, but negligible AC feedback\n* since Rfb >> Zout of OTA\nRfb vout vinn 100G\n\n* Instantiate OTA\nXota vinp vinn vout vdd vss vbn vbcn vbp vbcp ota_foldcasc\nCL vout 0 10p\n\n.ac dec 100 1 100Meg\n\n.control\n  run\n\n  echo \"\"\n  echo \"======================================================\"\n  echo \"  AC OPEN-LOOP — VibroSense OTA\"\n  echo \"======================================================\"\n\n  * DC operating point\n  echo \"--- DC Point ---\"\n  * Gain\n  meas ac gain_db MAX vdb(vout)\n  print gain_db\n\n  * UGB\n  meas ac ugb WHEN vdb(vout)=0 FALL=1\n  print ugb\n\n  * Phase at UGB\n  meas ac phase_at_ugb FIND vp(vout) AT=ugb\n  print phase_at_ugb\n\n  * Phase margin\n  let pm = phase_at_ugb + 180\n  print pm\n\n  * Gain at -180 degrees\n  meas ac freq_180 WHEN vp(vout)=-180 FALL=1\n  meas ac gain_180 FIND vdb(vout) AT=freq_180\n  let gm_db = -gain_180\n  print gm_db\n\n  * Some spot frequencies\n  meas ac gain_1hz FIND vdb(vout) AT=1\n  meas ac gain_100hz FIND vdb(vout) AT=100\n  meas ac gain_1k FIND vdb(vout) AT=1000\n  meas ac gain_10k FIND vdb(vout) AT=10000\n  meas ac gain_100k FIND vdb(vout) AT=100000\n  echo \"\"\n  echo \"Gain at 1Hz: $&gain_1hz dB\"\n  echo \"Gain at 100Hz: $&gain_100hz dB\"\n  echo \"Gain at 1kHz: $&gain_1k dB\"\n  echo \"Gain at 10kHz: $&gain_10k dB\"\n  echo \"Gain at 100kHz: $&gain_100k dB\"\n\n  * Phase at spot frequencies\n  meas ac ph_1hz FIND vp(vout) AT=1\n  meas ac ph_1k FIND vp(vout) AT=1000\n  meas ac ph_10k FIND vp(vout) AT=10000\n  echo \"Phase at 1Hz: $&ph_1hz deg\"\n  echo \"Phase at 1kHz: $&ph_1k deg\"\n  echo \"Phase at 10kHz: $&ph_10k deg\"\n\n  echo \"======================================================\"\n\n  wrdata bode_data vdb(vout) vp(vout)\n\n  quit\n.endc\n\n.end\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1743,"cache_read_input_tokens":250243,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1743},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01e4b3b1-6a11-48e6-b3e7-40758ef8985d","uuid":"8cc6a124-279b-437f-92f1-8c1e78908b1c"}
