{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01VaAECajMgyu1pRD3SRvTZ8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still negative gain everywhere. The maximum is -44 dB at 1.3 kHz. The phase is near 0° at all frequencies. This is not an amplifier output — this looks like a straight-through path or an attenuator.\n\nI think the issue is with the 100G ohm feedback resistor. At DC, 100G is very high and might not provide adequate feedback to set the operating point. Let me check the DC operating point first.\n\nActually, Rfb = 100G ohm from vout to vinn. \n\nWith the feedback resistor that large, the current flowing through it is essentially zero, so it barely influences the gate voltage of M2. But the real question is whether the feedback loop can actually force the output to the expected operating point — with finite gain, the output will deviate from the ideal 0.9V.\n\nThe core issue is that the open-loop output is railing at either 0.055V or 1.76V, and the 100G resistor provides almost no DC feedback current to pull it back to mid-rail. Even reducing the feedback resistor to 10M would strengthen the feedback without significantly affecting AC gain, but the fundamental problem remains: the biasing is pushing the output to the rails where the devices are in triode and the small-signal gain collapses. I need to adjust the biasing to keep the operating point in the saturation region.\n\nWith a smaller feedback resistor like 1M, I'd be measuring closed-loop gain (≈0dB) rather than open-loop gain, which defeats the purpose. The inductor-based approach might actually be the way forward—the earlier measurement showed 31dB, which suggests it was working. Let me revisit that method and verify the DC operating point is stable.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":455,"cache_read_input_tokens":254509,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":455},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01e4b3b1-6a11-48e6-b3e7-40758ef8985d","uuid":"8fa90f7d-672b-4b63-bf1b-9a3056a3df92"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01VaAECajMgyu1pRD3SRvTZ8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Rfb=100G doesn't establish the DC point properly. Let me go back to the inductor approach that gave 33 dB, but use Vbp=0.82 where the feedback config had Vout≈0.93V. And add proper diagnostic output."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":455,"cache_read_input_tokens":254509,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":455},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01e4b3b1-6a11-48e6-b3e7-40758ef8985d","uuid":"480fab9b-21d6-4f5e-b750-433bad25412b"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01VaAECajMgyu1pRD3SRvTZ8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_012T7V23V6hcqESPKMJNYZEV","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/vibrosense/01_ota/tb_ota_ac.spice","content":"* ============================================================\n* TB01: AC Open-Loop Analysis — VibroSense OTA\n* Method: Lfb (1GH) sets DC OP via unity-gain feedback,\n*         AC open-loop (Lfb is high-Z at signal freqs)\n* ============================================================\n\n.lib \"sky130_minimal.lib.spice\" tt\n.include \"ota_foldcasc.spice\"\n\n.param vdd_val = 1.8\n.param vcm_val = 0.9\n\nVdd vdd 0 dc {vdd_val}\nVss vss 0 dc 0\n\n* Bias\nMbn vbn vbn 0 0 sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8__model W=4u L=4u nf=1\nIbias vdd vbn dc 500n\nVbcn vbcn 0 dc 0.80\nMbp vbp vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8__model W=8u L=1u nf=2\nIbp vbp 0 dc 500n\nVbcp vbcp 0 dc 0.85\n\n* Input: Vcm + AC stimulus\nVcm vcm_node 0 dc {vcm_val}\nVac vinp vcm_node dc 0 ac 1\n\n* DC feedback: inductor from vout to vinn\n* At DC: L is short → vinn = vout → unity-gain → Vout ≈ Vinp = 0.9V\n* At AC: L is open → open loop\nLfb vout vinn 1G\n\n* OTA\nXota vinp vinn vout vdd vss vbn vbcn vbp vbcp ota_foldcasc\nCL vout 0 10p\n\n.ac dec 100 0.1 100Meg\n\n.control\n  run\n\n  echo \"\"\n  echo \"======================================================\"\n  echo \"  AC OPEN-LOOP — VibroSense OTA (Lfb method)\"\n  echo \"======================================================\"\n\n  * Find gain at various frequencies\n  meas ac gain_01hz FIND vdb(vout) AT=0.1\n  meas ac gain_1hz FIND vdb(vout) AT=1\n  meas ac gain_10hz FIND vdb(vout) AT=10\n  meas ac gain_100hz FIND vdb(vout) AT=100\n  meas ac gain_1k FIND vdb(vout) AT=1000\n  meas ac gain_10k FIND vdb(vout) AT=10000\n  meas ac gain_100k FIND vdb(vout) AT=100000\n\n  echo \"Gain at 0.1Hz: $&gain_01hz dB\"\n  echo \"Gain at 1Hz: $&gain_1hz dB\"\n  echo \"Gain at 10Hz: $&gain_10hz dB\"\n  echo \"Gain at 100Hz: $&gain_100hz dB\"\n  echo \"Gain at 1kHz: $&gain_1k dB\"\n  echo \"Gain at 10kHz: $&gain_10k dB\"\n  echo \"Gain at 100kHz: $&gain_100k dB\"\n\n  * Phase\n  meas ac ph_1hz FIND vp(vout) AT=1\n  meas ac ph_1k FIND vp(vout) AT=1000\n  meas ac ph_100k FIND vp(vout) AT=100000\n  echo \"Phase at 1Hz: $&ph_1hz deg\"\n  echo \"Phase at 1kHz: $&ph_1k deg\"\n  echo \"Phase at 100kHz: $&ph_100k deg\"\n\n  * Max gain and UGB\n  meas ac gain_db MAX vdb(vout)\n  meas ac ugb WHEN vdb(vout)=0 FALL=1\n\n  echo \"\"\n  echo \"MAX Gain: $&gain_db dB\"\n  echo \"UGB: $&ugb Hz\"\n\n  * Phase margin if UGB found\n  meas ac phase_ugb FIND vp(vout) AT=ugb\n  echo \"Phase at UGB: $&phase_ugb deg\"\n\n  echo \"======================================================\"\n\n  wrdata bode_data vdb(vout) vp(vout)\n\n  quit\n.endc\n\n.end\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":455,"cache_read_input_tokens":254509,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":455},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01e4b3b1-6a11-48e6-b3e7-40758ef8985d","uuid":"43194b1e-c6fe-479b-8122-3a997933c849"}
