{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01WkQspnTut3aNVu3XdJmGUR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Rout = 601 kOhm (0.6 MOhm) at this operating point. This is VERY low for a cascode. \n\nBut wait — this Rout is measured at the open-loop operating point where the output is railed (Vout ≈ 0.05V based on the earlier OP test with both inputs at 0.9V). At this operating point, many devices are in triode, explaining the low output impedance.\n\nThe .tf is computing the small-signal impedance at the DC operating point established by the circuit. Since both inputs are at 0.9V and there's no feedback, the output is at one rail.\n\n\nI need to measure Rout at the correct operating point where Vout ≈ 0.9V instead. The simplest approach is to force the output to that voltage using a voltage source, then measure the current drawn to find the small-signal output impedance.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2020,"cache_read_input_tokens":281294,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2020},"output_tokens":12,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01e4b3b1-6a11-48e6-b3e7-40758ef8985d","uuid":"9d009add-54c0-4c89-8231-9f22bc845354"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01WkQspnTut3aNVu3XdJmGUR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01LXTUicEjN3mfuCBKiwrcJr","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cat > rout_test2.spice << 'EOF'\n.lib \"sky130_minimal.lib.spice\" tt\n.include \"ota_foldcasc.spice\"\n\nVdd vdd 0 dc 1.8\nVss vss 0 dc 0\nMbn vbn vbn 0 0 sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8__model W=4u L=4u nf=1\nIbias vdd vbn dc 500n\nVbcn vbcn 0 dc 0.80\nMbp vbp vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8__model W=8u L=1u nf=2\nIbp vbp 0 dc 500n\nVbcp vbcp 0 dc 0.70\n\n* Inputs at 0.9V, output forced to 0.9V region\nVinp vinp 0 dc 0.9\nVinn vinn 0 dc 0.9\n\nXota vinp vinn vout vdd vss vbn vbcn vbp vbcp ota_foldcasc\n\n* Force output and sweep\nVout_force vout 0 dc 0.9\n\n* Sweep output to get Rout at the operating point\n.dc Vout_force 0.85 0.95 0.001\n\n.control\n  run\n  * Current into output = -i(Vout_force)  \n  * dI/dV at 0.9V gives the output conductance\n  meas dc i_low FIND i(Vout_force) AT=0.899\n  meas dc i_high FIND i(Vout_force) AT=0.901\n  let gout = (i_high - i_low) / 0.002\n  let rout = 1 / gout\n  echo \"Output conductance: $&gout S\"\n  echo \"Output resistance: $&rout Ohm\"\n  echo \"\"\n  * Also get the operating point data at Vout=0.9\n  alter Vout_force dc = 0.9\n  op\n  echo \"At Vout=0.9V forced:\"\n  echo \"M2 gds=$&@m.xota.m2[gds] Id=$&@m.xota.m2[id] Vds=$&@m.xota.m2[vds]\"\n  echo \"M4 gds=$&@m.xota.m4[gds] Vds=$&@m.xota.m4[vds] Vdsat=$&@m.xota.m4[vdsat]\"\n  echo \"M6 gds=$&@m.xota.m6[gds] gm=$&@m.xota.m6[gm] Vds=$&@m.xota.m6[vds]\"\n  echo \"M8 gds=$&@m.xota.m8[gds] gm=$&@m.xota.m8[gm] Vds=$&@m.xota.m8[vds]\"\n  echo \"M10 gds=$&@m.xota.m10[gds] Vds=$&@m.xota.m10[vds]\"\n  quit\n.endc\n.end\nEOF\n/usr/bin/ngspice -b rout_test2.spice 2>&1 | grep -E \"^(Output|At |M[0-9])\" | head -15","description":"Measure Rout with forced operating point","timeout":120000},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2020,"cache_read_input_tokens":281294,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2020},"output_tokens":12,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01e4b3b1-6a11-48e6-b3e7-40758ef8985d","uuid":"d7ed7545-0212-4b40-8c20-469253e12511"}
