{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01MNqhvEjyLgkjYYTQd7g8TM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The \"Dsub = -0.197221 is negative\" error is back. This happens with the PFET model at certain geometries. It's related to the DIBL parameter in BSIM4.\n\nThe issue is that M5/M6 at W=8u L=1u nf=2 (finger width = 4u, L=1u) falls in a bin where the model parameters give a negative Dsub value. This is a known issue with some PDK model extractions.\n\nLet me check which bin is causing the problem. For PFET at L=1u W=4u (per finger):- L=1u falls in the [0.5, 1.0] bin\n\n\nI'm trying different channel lengths to avoid this problematic parameter set—maybe L=0.8u instead of L=1.0u would work, or I could go back to L=0.5u which was stable before. The issue seems specific to M5/M6 at this geometry rather than a general problem, since M3/M4 worked fine at L=1u with W=8u, so I need to figure out if it's the Mbp bias device causing the trouble.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":236,"cache_read_input_tokens":304403,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":236},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01e4b3b1-6a11-48e6-b3e7-40758ef8985d","uuid":"6cf17afa-5e5b-4f3a-9023-91e1eb97efe3"}
