{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01RnHaDNDoYjtYGfLNPAUuAH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The error is from NFET model bin 23, not PFET. The NMOS model bin 23 has a negative Dsub parameter. M7/M8 at W=4u L=1u falls in this bin.\n\nLet me check which bin covers L=1u W=4u/2fingers=2u per finger for NFET.\n\nNFET bins L ranges: [0.15,0.18], [0.18,0.25], [0.25,0.5], [0.5,1.0], [1.0,2.0], etc.\nL=1u is at the boundary between [0.5,1.0] and [1.0,2.0]. Depending on the exact boundary definition (lmin ≤ L ≤ lmax or lmin < L < lmax), L=1u might fall in either bin.\n\n\nI could try adjusting L to avoid bin 23 entirely—either L=0.8u to stay safely in the [0.5,1.0] range or L=1.5u to clearly land in [1.0,2.0]. But the simplest approach is to revert M7/M8 back to L=0.5u since that worked before, and just increase M5/M6 instead.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":599,"cache_read_input_tokens":304639,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":599},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01e4b3b1-6a11-48e6-b3e7-40758ef8985d","uuid":"fc699ac9-e746-4c86-8356-e3fb0c3770bc"}
