{"type":"system","subtype":"task_progress","task_id":"a747190c2db75e60d","tool_use_id":"toolu_01EZLvWR7y8upt6isXr71TxJ","description":"Writing tb_ota_cmrr.spice","usage":{"total_tokens":23190,"tool_uses":11,"duration_ms":114981},"last_tool_name":"Write","uuid":"775b756f-0efd-4c44-9654-8acb17ad6152","session_id":"01e4b3b1-6a11-48e6-b3e7-40758ef8985d"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019tkgPBjLr3mRq68i6uLsNi","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01WBhWNCinspvv98auxaUPk4","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/vibrosense/01_ota/tb_ota_cmrr.spice","content":"* CMRR Analysis - VibroSense OTA\n* Common-Mode Rejection Ratio = A_diff(dB) - A_cm(dB)\n.lib \"sky130_minimal.lib.spice\" tt\n.include \"ota_foldcasc.spice\"\n\nVdd vdd 0 dc 1.8\nVss vss 0 dc 0\nMbn vbn vbn 0 0 sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8__model W=4u L=4u nf=1\nIbias vdd vbn dc 500n\nVbcn vbcn 0 dc 0.80\nMbp vbp vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8__model W=8u L=1u nf=2\nIbp vbp 0 dc 500n\nVbcp vbcp 0 dc 0.70\n\n* Tie both inputs together and apply the common-mode AC signal\n* Vcm_dc sets DC operating point; Vcm_ac adds the AC stimulus\nVcm_dc vcm 0 dc 0.9\nVcm_ac vinp vcm dc 0 ac 1\n* Inverting input tied to the same node: both inputs driven identically\nVtie vinn vinp dc 0\n\n* Unity-gain feedback for DC bias stability (Lfb connects vout back to vinn)\n* With vinn already tied to vinp, we add the feedback via inductor\n* to ensure the output has a defined DC operating point.\n* Note: vinn is already connected to vinp by Vtie;\n* Lfb is removed here since vinn is already hard-tied.\n* The DC bias comes from the common-mode input level (0.9V).\n\nXota vinp vinn vout vdd vss vbn vbcn vbp vbcp ota_foldcasc\nCL vout 0 10p\n\n* Sweep from 1Hz to 100MHz\n.ac dec 100 1 100Meg\n\n.control\n  run\n\n  * Common-mode gain = V(vout) / Vcm_ac\n  * Since Vcm_ac = 1 (AC), vdb(vout) directly gives Acm in dB\n  let acm_db = vdb(vout)\n\n  * Spot values of common-mode gain\n  meas ac acm_1hz   FIND vdb(vout) AT=1\n  meas ac acm_1k    FIND vdb(vout) AT=1000\n  meas ac acm_10k   FIND vdb(vout) AT=10000\n  meas ac acm_100k  FIND vdb(vout) AT=100000\n  meas ac acm_1meg  FIND vdb(vout) AT=1000000\n\n  * DC common-mode gain (lowest frequency point)\n  meas ac acm_dc MAX vdb(vout) FROM=1 TO=10\n\n  echo \"\"\n  echo \"======================================================\"\n  echo \"  CMRR Analysis Results\"\n  echo \"  (Both inputs driven together; Vout/Vcm)\"\n  echo \"  CMRR(f) = A_diff(f) - A_cm(f)  [dB]\"\n  echo \"======================================================\"\n  echo \"Common-mode gain A_cm:\"\n  echo \"  1 Hz:    $&acm_1hz dB\"\n  echo \"  1 kHz:   $&acm_1k dB\"\n  echo \"  10 kHz:  $&acm_10k dB\"\n  echo \"  100 kHz: $&acm_100k dB\"\n  echo \"  1 MHz:   $&acm_1meg dB\"\n  echo \"\"\n  echo \"DC common-mode gain (1-10 Hz): $&acm_dc dB\"\n  echo \"\"\n  echo \"Note: CMRR = diff_gain_dB - acm_dB\"\n  echo \"      Run tb_ota_ac.spice for diff gain, then subtract.\"\n  echo \"======================================================\"\n\n  wrdata cmrr_data vdb(vout) vp(vout)\n  quit\n.endc\n.end\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1087,"cache_read_input_tokens":21785,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1087,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":72,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01EZLvWR7y8upt6isXr71TxJ","session_id":"01e4b3b1-6a11-48e6-b3e7-40758ef8985d","uuid":"a928c4c5-c2ac-47c8-838a-15177952da10"}
