{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EZLvWR7y8upt6isXr71TxJ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 6 files are present and correctly structured. Here is a summary of what was created:\n\n---\n\nAll 6 testbenches written to `/home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/vibrosense/01_ota/`:\n\n**tb_ota_op.spice** — Replaced the existing file. Uses `Lfb vout vinn 1T` (inductor feedback, matching the AC testbench pattern) instead of the `Rfb` resistor that was there before. Prints all 7 device parameters (Vgs, Vth, Vds, Vdsat, Id, gm, gds) for each of M1–M13 via `@m.xota.mN[param]` accessor paths.\n\n**tb_ota_dc.spice** — Uses `Vinn vinn vout dc 0` (voltage source as a direct wire, appropriate for DC sweep since there is no AC path concern). Sweeps `Vinp` 0→1.8 V in 1 mV steps, measures and reports Vout_max, Vout_min, and swing.\n\n**tb_ota_tran.spice** — Uses `Lfb` feedback. PWL source gives a 100 mV step (0.9→1.0 V) at t=10 µs with a 20 ns ramp. `.tran 10n 100u`. Measures 10%–90% rise time and computes slew rate in V/s, peak overshoot, and settled output.\n\n**tb_ota_noise.spice** — Mirrors the AC testbench exactly (Vcm + Vac AC source, Lfb feedback). Uses `.noise V(vout) Vac dec 100 1 1Meg`. Reports `inoise_spectrum` and `onoise_spectrum` at 1 kHz and 10 kHz.\n\n**tb_ota_psrr.spice** — `Vdd vdd 0 dc 1.8 ac 1` injects AC on the supply. Both inputs at Vcm=0.9 V DC; `Lfb` holds the output. `.ac dec 100 1 100Meg`. Reports VDD-to-output gain at key frequencies; PSRR is obtained by subtracting this from the differential gain run in `tb_ota_ac.spice`.\n\n**tb_ota_cmrr.spice** — `Vtie vinn vinp dc 0` ties both inputs together; `Vcm_ac` drives the common-mode with `ac 1`. No `Lfb` needed since the inputs are hard-shorted. `.ac dec 100 1 100Meg`. Reports common-mode gain A_cm at key frequencies; CMRR obtained by subtracting A_cm from the differential gain."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a747190c2db75e60d (use SendMessage with to: 'a747190c2db75e60d' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 26138\ntool_uses: 13\nduration_ms: 134990</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01e4b3b1-6a11-48e6-b3e7-40758ef8985d","uuid":"71bb349b-f33c-48fb-9d41-0a6477f8d117","timestamp":"2026-03-22T23:03:25.403Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"You are working on an analog OTA design in /home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/vibrosense/01_ota/. \n\nRead the existing files tb_ota_ac.spice and ota_foldcasc.spice to understand the testbench structure and device models, then create the following testbenches. Each testbench should follow the same pattern:\n- .lib \"sky130_minimal.lib.spice\" tt\n- .include \"ota_foldcasc.spice\"  \n- Same bias generation (Mbn, Ibias, Vbcn=0.80, Mbp, Ibp, Vbcp=0.70)\n- Model names: sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8__model, sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8__model (M prefix)\n\nCreate these files:\n\n1. **tb_ota_op.spice** - Operating point verification\n   - Unity-gain feedback (Lfb vout vinn 1T, Vinp dc 0.9)\n   - .op analysis\n   - Print Vgs, Vth, Vds, Vdsat, Id, gm, gds for all 13 transistors (M1-M13)\n   - The device access path is @m.xota.m1[id] etc.\n\n2. **tb_ota_dc.spice** - DC sweep (output swing)\n   - Unity-gain feedback (connect vout to vinn)\n   - Sweep Vinp from 0 to 1.8V in 1mV steps\n   - Measure max/min output voltage and swing\n\n3. **tb_ota_tran.spice** - Transient step response\n   - Unity-gain feedback\n   - 100mV step on Vinp at t=10us (from 0.9V to 1.0V)\n   - .tran 10n 100u\n   - Measure slew rate\n\n4. **tb_ota_noise.spice** - Noise analysis\n   - Same AC testbench config (Lfb feedback, AC source on Vinp)\n   - .noise V(vout) Vac dec 100 1 1Meg\n   - Print inoise_spectrum at 1kHz and 10kHz\n\n5. **tb_ota_psrr.spice** - PSRR\n   - Both inputs at Vcm=0.9V (no feedback needed, just AC on VDD)\n   - Unity-gain feedback for DC bias (Lfb)\n   - AC source on Vdd: Vdd vdd 0 dc 1.8 ac 1\n   - .ac dec 100 1 100Meg\n   - PSRR = gain_db - vdd_to_output_gain\n\n6. **tb_ota_cmrr.spice** - CMRR\n   - Tie both inputs together\n   - Unity-gain feedback for DC bias\n   - AC source on common input\n   - .ac dec 100 1 100Meg\n   - Measure common-mode gain, CMRR = diff_gain - cm_gain\n\nWrite all 6 files. DO NOT modify program.md, specs.json, requirements.md, or ota_foldcasc.spice.","agentId":"a747190c2db75e60d","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 6 files are present and correctly structured. Here is a summary of what was created:\n\n---\n\nAll 6 testbenches written to `/home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/vibrosense/01_ota/`:\n\n**tb_ota_op.spice** — Replaced the existing file. Uses `Lfb vout vinn 1T` (inductor feedback, matching the AC testbench pattern) instead of the `Rfb` resistor that was there before. Prints all 7 device parameters (Vgs, Vth, Vds, Vdsat, Id, gm, gds) for each of M1–M13 via `@m.xota.mN[param]` accessor paths.\n\n**tb_ota_dc.spice** — Uses `Vinn vinn vout dc 0` (voltage source as a direct wire, appropriate for DC sweep since there is no AC path concern). Sweeps `Vinp` 0→1.8 V in 1 mV steps, measures and reports Vout_max, Vout_min, and swing.\n\n**tb_ota_tran.spice** — Uses `Lfb` feedback. PWL source gives a 100 mV step (0.9→1.0 V) at t=10 µs with a 20 ns ramp. `.tran 10n 100u`. Measures 10%–90% rise time and computes slew rate in V/s, peak overshoot, and settled output.\n\n**tb_ota_noise.spice** — Mirrors the AC testbench exactly (Vcm + Vac AC source, Lfb feedback). Uses `.noise V(vout) Vac dec 100 1 1Meg`. Reports `inoise_spectrum` and `onoise_spectrum` at 1 kHz and 10 kHz.\n\n**tb_ota_psrr.spice** — `Vdd vdd 0 dc 1.8 ac 1` injects AC on the supply. Both inputs at Vcm=0.9 V DC; `Lfb` holds the output. `.ac dec 100 1 100Meg`. Reports VDD-to-output gain at key frequencies; PSRR is obtained by subtracting this from the differential gain run in `tb_ota_ac.spice`.\n\n**tb_ota_cmrr.spice** — `Vtie vinn vinp dc 0` ties both inputs together; `Vcm_ac` drives the common-mode with `ac 1`. No `Lfb` needed since the inputs are hard-shorted. `.ac dec 100 1 100Meg`. Reports common-mode gain A_cm at key frequencies; CMRR obtained by subtracting A_cm from the differential gain."}],"totalDurationMs":134990,"totalTokens":26138,"totalToolUseCount":13,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":843,"cache_read_input_tokens":24617,"output_tokens":677,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":843},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
