{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Lkz39safukyxg28ufQkY7Y","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→* Transient Step Response - VibroSense OTA\n     2→.lib \"sky130_minimal.lib.spice\" tt\n     3→.include \"ota_foldcasc.spice\"\n     4→\n     5→Vdd vdd 0 dc 1.8\n     6→Vss vss 0 dc 0\n     7→Mbn vbn vbn 0 0 sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8__model W=4u L=4u nf=1\n     8→Ibias vdd vbn dc 500n\n     9→Vbcn vbcn 0 dc 0.80\n    10→Mbp vbp vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8__model W=8u L=1u nf=2\n    11→Ibp vbp 0 dc 500n\n    12→Vbcp vbcp 0 dc 0.70\n    13→\n    14→* Unity-gain feedback via ideal inductor (DC short, passes step cleanly)\n    15→Lfb vout vinn 1T\n    16→\n    17→* 100mV step at t=10us: 0.9V -> 1.0V\n    18→* PWL: 0V=0.9V, step up to 1.0V at 10us (10ns rise time)\n    19→Vinp vinp 0 pwl(0 0.9 9.99u 0.9 10.01u 1.0)\n    20→\n    21→Xota vinp vinn vout vdd vss vbn vbcn vbp vbcp ota_foldcasc\n    22→CL vout 0 10p\n    23→\n    24→.tran 10n 100u\n    25→\n    26→.control\n    27→  run\n    28→\n    29→  * Measure slew rate on rising edge\n    30→  * 10%-90% of 100mV step = 10mV to 90mV above 0.9V => 0.91V to 0.99V\n    31→  meas tran t10 WHEN v(vout)=0.91 RISE=1\n    32→  meas tran t90 WHEN v(vout)=0.99 RISE=1\n    33→  let delta_t = t90 - t10\n    34→  let delta_v = 0.99 - 0.91\n    35→  let slew_rate = delta_v / delta_t\n    36→\n    37→  * Settling: measure final value at end of simulation\n    38→  meas tran vout_final FIND v(vout) AT=100u\n    39→\n    40→  * Overshoot: max value after the step\n    41→  meas tran vout_peak MAX v(vout) FROM=10u TO=100u\n    42→  let overshoot_mv = (vout_peak - 1.0) * 1000\n    43→\n    44→  echo \"\"\n    45→  echo \"======================================================\"\n    46→  echo \"  Transient Step Response (100mV step at t=10us)\"\n    47→  echo \"======================================================\"\n    48→  echo \"10%->90% rise time (t10 to t90):\"\n    49→  echo \"  t10 = $&t10 s\"\n    50→  echo \"  t90 = $&t90 s\"\n    51→  echo \"  delta_t = $&delta_t s\"\n    52→  echo \"Slew rate (10-90%): $&slew_rate V/s\"\n    53→  echo \"Peak output: $&vout_peak V\"\n    54→  echo \"Overshoot: $&overshoot_mv mV\"\n    55→  echo \"Final settled output (t=100us): $&vout_final V\"\n    56→  echo \"======================================================\"\n    57→\n    58→  wrdata tran_step_data v(vout) v(vinp)\n    59→  quit\n    60→.endc\n    61→.end\n    62→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01e4b3b1-6a11-48e6-b3e7-40758ef8985d","uuid":"26025318-82e5-4b01-bd6e-fa5eabf5d25f","timestamp":"2026-03-22T23:03:53.940Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/vibrosense/01_ota/tb_ota_tran.spice","content":"* Transient Step Response - VibroSense OTA\n.lib \"sky130_minimal.lib.spice\" tt\n.include \"ota_foldcasc.spice\"\n\nVdd vdd 0 dc 1.8\nVss vss 0 dc 0\nMbn vbn vbn 0 0 sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8__model W=4u L=4u nf=1\nIbias vdd vbn dc 500n\nVbcn vbcn 0 dc 0.80\nMbp vbp vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8__model W=8u L=1u nf=2\nIbp vbp 0 dc 500n\nVbcp vbcp 0 dc 0.70\n\n* Unity-gain feedback via ideal inductor (DC short, passes step cleanly)\nLfb vout vinn 1T\n\n* 100mV step at t=10us: 0.9V -> 1.0V\n* PWL: 0V=0.9V, step up to 1.0V at 10us (10ns rise time)\nVinp vinp 0 pwl(0 0.9 9.99u 0.9 10.01u 1.0)\n\nXota vinp vinn vout vdd vss vbn vbcn vbp vbcp ota_foldcasc\nCL vout 0 10p\n\n.tran 10n 100u\n\n.control\n  run\n\n  * Measure slew rate on rising edge\n  * 10%-90% of 100mV step = 10mV to 90mV above 0.9V => 0.91V to 0.99V\n  meas tran t10 WHEN v(vout)=0.91 RISE=1\n  meas tran t90 WHEN v(vout)=0.99 RISE=1\n  let delta_t = t90 - t10\n  let delta_v = 0.99 - 0.91\n  let slew_rate = delta_v / delta_t\n\n  * Settling: measure final value at end of simulation\n  meas tran vout_final FIND v(vout) AT=100u\n\n  * Overshoot: max value after the step\n  meas tran vout_peak MAX v(vout) FROM=10u TO=100u\n  let overshoot_mv = (vout_peak - 1.0) * 1000\n\n  echo \"\"\n  echo \"======================================================\"\n  echo \"  Transient Step Response (100mV step at t=10us)\"\n  echo \"======================================================\"\n  echo \"10%->90% rise time (t10 to t90):\"\n  echo \"  t10 = $&t10 s\"\n  echo \"  t90 = $&t90 s\"\n  echo \"  delta_t = $&delta_t s\"\n  echo \"Slew rate (10-90%): $&slew_rate V/s\"\n  echo \"Peak output: $&vout_peak V\"\n  echo \"Overshoot: $&overshoot_mv mV\"\n  echo \"Final settled output (t=100us): $&vout_final V\"\n  echo \"======================================================\"\n\n  wrdata tran_step_data v(vout) v(vinp)\n  quit\n.endc\n.end\n","numLines":62,"startLine":1,"totalLines":62}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01DnDbqXrdvRwrjxiKAoLanQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The transient testbench uses Lfb (1T inductor) for feedback. At DC, the inductor is a short, so vinn = vout. This should work for the DC operating point.\n\nBut the problem is that when the step happens at t=10us, the inductor has impedance Z_L = j*w*L = j*2*pi*f*1e12. For a step signal (containing many frequencies), the inductor's impedance varies. At very low frequencies (like the DC component), the inductor is a short — the feedback is active. At higher frequencies (the step's fast edges), the inductor is open — no feedback.\n\n\nDuring the step transition, the 1T inductor presents essentially infinite impedance at the step's frequency content, completely breaking the feedback loop. The OTA then operates open-loop with its massive gain, causing the output to rail from even tiny input perturbations. I need to find a way to maintain feedback stability during transients.\n\nFor the transient testbench, I should use a direct wire connection from the output back to the inverting input instead of the inductor, since the inductor approach only works for AC analysis. Let me update the testbench to use this direct feedback path.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1211,"cache_read_input_tokens":319984,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1211},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01e4b3b1-6a11-48e6-b3e7-40758ef8985d","uuid":"904b5b9b-96b2-4d5c-b888-0e8662645eab"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01DnDbqXrdvRwrjxiKAoLanQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The 1T inductor doesn't work for transient — it's too slow to provide feedback during the step. Need direct wire feedback."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1211,"cache_read_input_tokens":319984,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1211},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01e4b3b1-6a11-48e6-b3e7-40758ef8985d","uuid":"e70b5895-ae86-46a6-8007-e4687a8194e5"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01DnDbqXrdvRwrjxiKAoLanQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_011mcHkcwMpGKPkvZRkJMMxq","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/vibrosense/01_ota/tb_ota_tran.spice","content":"* Transient Step Response - VibroSense OTA\n.lib \"sky130_minimal.lib.spice\" tt\n.include \"ota_foldcasc.spice\"\n\nVdd vdd 0 dc 1.8\nVss vss 0 dc 0\nMbn vbn vbn 0 0 sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8__model W=4u L=4u nf=1\nIbias vdd vbn dc 500n\nVbcn vbcn 0 dc 0.80\nMbp vbp vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8__model W=8u L=1u nf=2\nIbp vbp 0 dc 500n\nVbcp vbcp 0 dc 0.70\n\n* Direct unity-gain feedback (wire from vout to vinn)\nVfb vout vinn dc 0\n\n* 100mV step at t=10us: 0.9V -> 1.0V\nVinp vinp 0 pwl(0 0.9 9.99u 0.9 10.01u 1.0)\n\nXota vinp vinn vout vdd vss vbn vbcn vbp vbcp ota_foldcasc\nCL vout 0 10p\n\n.tran 10n 100u\n\n.control\n  run\n\n  * Measure slew rate on rising edge\n  meas tran t10 WHEN v(vout)=0.91 RISE=1\n  meas tran t90 WHEN v(vout)=0.99 RISE=1\n\n  * Settling: measure final value\n  meas tran vout_final FIND v(vout) AT=100u\n\n  * Overshoot\n  meas tran vout_peak MAX v(vout) FROM=10u TO=100u\n\n  echo \"\"\n  echo \"======================================================\"\n  echo \"  Transient Step Response (100mV step at t=10us)\"\n  echo \"======================================================\"\n\n  * Slew rate\n  let delta_t = t90 - t10\n  let sr = 0.08 / delta_t\n  echo \"t10=$&t10 t90=$&t90\"\n  echo \"Slew rate: $&sr V/s\"\n\n  * Convert to mV/us\n  let sr_mvus = sr * 1e-6 * 1e3\n  echo \"Slew rate: $&sr_mvus mV/us\"\n\n  echo \"Peak: $&vout_peak V\"\n  echo \"Final: $&vout_final V\"\n  let overshoot = (vout_peak - 1.0) * 1000\n  echo \"Overshoot: $&overshoot mV\"\n  echo \"======================================================\"\n\n  wrdata tran_step_data v(vout) v(vinp)\n  quit\n.endc\n.end\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1211,"cache_read_input_tokens":319984,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1211},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01e4b3b1-6a11-48e6-b3e7-40758ef8985d","uuid":"1c48301f-c84d-4b11-9d7f-425cd029d26a"}
