{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01H6bdkUCW9EX74Td5BENe6i","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The t10 measurement (when v(vout) crosses 0.91V) failed because the output was already above 0.91V before the step. The initial DC operating point has Vout ≈ 0.92V, so v(vout) starts above 0.91V.\n\nLet me adjust the measurement thresholds. With a step from 0.9V to 1.0V, and the OTA in unity-gain feedback:\n- Initial Vout ≈ 0.92V (due to offset)\n- After step: Vout → ~1.02V (0.9V + 100mV step + offset)\n\n\n- 10% of the 100mV step gives a t10 threshold of 0.93V\n- 90% of the step gives a t90 threshold of 1.01V\n\nThe t90 measurement came in at 16.27us, which is about 6.27us after the step occurs at 10us. So the output is taking roughly 6 microseconds to reach 90% of its final value.\n\nThe slew rate works out to about 16 mV/us (100mV divided by 6.27us), which actually exceeds the 10 mV/us target I was aiming for. Looking at the actual values, the peak is around 1.019V with no meaningful overshoot relative to the final value, though there's about 19mV of overshoot from the 1.0V target. The response isn't ideal, but the slew rate is acceptable. I'll move on to testing the noise performance and other testbenches, then come back to refine these measurements later.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":358,"cache_read_input_tokens":322732,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":358},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01e4b3b1-6a11-48e6-b3e7-40758ef8985d","uuid":"7727c3c4-42b9-4b9d-869e-c9c5dfedf64f"}
