{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012t1iqcp29UwnB4eKVT5dE6","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→* Noise Analysis - VibroSense OTA\n     2→.lib \"sky130_minimal.lib.spice\" tt\n     3→.include \"ota_foldcasc.spice\"\n     4→\n     5→Vdd vdd 0 dc 1.8\n     6→Vss vss 0 dc 0\n     7→Mbn vbn vbn 0 0 sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8__model W=4u L=4u nf=1\n     8→Ibias vdd vbn dc 500n\n     9→Vbcn vbcn 0 dc 0.80\n    10→Mbp vbp vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8__model W=8u L=1u nf=2\n    11→Ibp vbp 0 dc 500n\n    12→Vbcp vbcp 0 dc 0.70\n    13→\n    14→* Same config as AC testbench: Vcm + AC source on vinp, inductor feedback\n    15→Vcm cm 0 dc 0.9\n    16→Vac vinp cm dc 0 ac 1\n    17→\n    18→* DC feedback via inductor (same as tb_ota_ac.spice)\n    19→Lfb vout vinn 1T\n    20→\n    21→Xota vinp vinn vout vdd vss vbn vbcn vbp vbcp ota_foldcasc\n    22→CL vout 0 10p\n    23→\n    24→* Noise analysis: output-referred noise at vout, input source Vac\n    25→* dec 100 points/decade, 1Hz to 1MHz\n    26→.noise V(vout) Vac dec 100 1 1Meg\n    27→\n    28→.control\n    29→  run\n    30→\n    31→  * Print input-referred noise spectrum at key frequencies\n    32→  meas noise inoise_1k   FIND inoise_spectrum AT=1000\n    33→  meas noise inoise_10k  FIND inoise_spectrum AT=10000\n    34→  meas noise onoise_1k   FIND onoise_spectrum AT=1000\n    35→  meas noise onoise_10k  FIND onoise_spectrum AT=10000\n    36→\n    37→  echo \"\"\n    38→  echo \"======================================================\"\n    39→  echo \"  Noise Analysis Results\"\n    40→  echo \"======================================================\"\n    41→  echo \"Input-referred noise density:\"\n    42→  echo \"  1 kHz:  $&inoise_1k  V/sqrt(Hz)\"\n    43→  echo \"  10 kHz: $&inoise_10k V/sqrt(Hz)\"\n    44→  echo \"\"\n    45→  echo \"Output-referred noise density:\"\n    46→  echo \"  1 kHz:  $&onoise_1k  V/sqrt(Hz)\"\n    47→  echo \"  10 kHz: $&onoise_10k V/sqrt(Hz)\"\n    48→  echo \"======================================================\"\n    49→\n    50→  wrdata noise_data inoise_spectrum onoise_spectrum\n    51→  quit\n    52→.endc\n    53→.end\n    54→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01e4b3b1-6a11-48e6-b3e7-40758ef8985d","uuid":"395d9b98-3ad0-4761-939e-6ea9e22deb49","timestamp":"2026-03-22T23:04:44.819Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/ubuntu/analog-ai-chips/vibrosense/01_ota/tb_ota_noise.spice","content":"* Noise Analysis - VibroSense OTA\n.lib \"sky130_minimal.lib.spice\" tt\n.include \"ota_foldcasc.spice\"\n\nVdd vdd 0 dc 1.8\nVss vss 0 dc 0\nMbn vbn vbn 0 0 sky130_fd_pr__nfet_01v8__model W=4u L=4u nf=1\nIbias vdd vbn dc 500n\nVbcn vbcn 0 dc 0.80\nMbp vbp vbp vdd vdd sky130_fd_pr__pfet_01v8__model W=8u L=1u nf=2\nIbp vbp 0 dc 500n\nVbcp vbcp 0 dc 0.70\n\n* Same config as AC testbench: Vcm + AC source on vinp, inductor feedback\nVcm cm 0 dc 0.9\nVac vinp cm dc 0 ac 1\n\n* DC feedback via inductor (same as tb_ota_ac.spice)\nLfb vout vinn 1T\n\nXota vinp vinn vout vdd vss vbn vbcn vbp vbcp ota_foldcasc\nCL vout 0 10p\n\n* Noise analysis: output-referred noise at vout, input source Vac\n* dec 100 points/decade, 1Hz to 1MHz\n.noise V(vout) Vac dec 100 1 1Meg\n\n.control\n  run\n\n  * Print input-referred noise spectrum at key frequencies\n  meas noise inoise_1k   FIND inoise_spectrum AT=1000\n  meas noise inoise_10k  FIND inoise_spectrum AT=10000\n  meas noise onoise_1k   FIND onoise_spectrum AT=1000\n  meas noise onoise_10k  FIND onoise_spectrum AT=10000\n\n  echo \"\"\n  echo \"======================================================\"\n  echo \"  Noise Analysis Results\"\n  echo \"======================================================\"\n  echo \"Input-referred noise density:\"\n  echo \"  1 kHz:  $&inoise_1k  V/sqrt(Hz)\"\n  echo \"  10 kHz: $&inoise_10k V/sqrt(Hz)\"\n  echo \"\"\n  echo \"Output-referred noise density:\"\n  echo \"  1 kHz:  $&onoise_1k  V/sqrt(Hz)\"\n  echo \"  10 kHz: $&onoise_10k V/sqrt(Hz)\"\n  echo \"======================================================\"\n\n  wrdata noise_data inoise_spectrum onoise_spectrum\n  quit\n.endc\n.end\n","numLines":54,"startLine":1,"totalLines":54}}}
